----------------------------------------------------------------------
-- Whole-model verification summary
----------------------------------------------------------------------

-- Summary 1: Model corrected to include concrete resource sig (BloodInventory) and permission assignments, enabling satisfiable operations.
-- Summary 2: Type errors fixed: replaced references to Blood_Inventory_Database (Interface) in target sets with BloodInventory (Resource).
-- Summary 3: Facts added to assign permissions to actors and set resource ownership/accessibility.
-- Summary 4: Core safety and behavioral assertions now properly typed and checkable.
-- Assumption 1: Blood inventory is modeled as a single aggregate resource (BloodInventory) rather than individual units.
-- Assumption 2: Only Blood_Bank_Manager has Write permission and access to BloodInventory; other actors have Read-only.
-- Assumption 3: Reservation timeout and cancellation are represented by state transitions only, without explicit temporal ordering.
-- Assumption 4: Each operation uses exactly two communication channels, one authenticated and one not, based on combined NFR facts.
-- Open issue 1: The model does not represent multiple individual blood units; aggregate resource limits fine-grained inventory tracking.
-- Open issue 2: Edge case assertion ec_safe_1 is tautological due to existing constraints (post is always in Post1+Post2+Post3).
-- Open issue 3: No temporal logic to enforce sequential state transitions (e.g., Pre1 must precede Post1, and then Post2); only static relations.
-- Open issue 4: The stronger permission function is defined but unused; could be removed or integrated into security assertions.


